  "prompt": "What Pok\u00e9mon hatches from Eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, different Pok\u00e9mon can hatch from Eggs depending on the Egg type. Here\u2019s the breakdown of Pok\u00e9mon that can currently hatch from Eggs as of the latest updates:\n\n### 1. **2 km Eggs**  \n- **Common Pok\u00e9mon:**  \n  - Magikarp, Wurmple, Lillipup, Purrloin, Pikipek, Bidoof, Starly, Pidove, Fletchling, Bounsweet, and more.  \n- **Event-exclusive Pok\u00e9mon may also appear during special events.**\n\n### 2. **5 km Eggs**  \n- **Common Pok\u00e9mon:**  \n  - Shinx, Ralts, Slakoth, Timburr, Tympole, Roggenrola, Petilil, Sandile, Larvesta, and more.  \n- **Event-exclusive Pok\u00e9mon may also appear during special events.**\n\n### 3. **7 km Eggs**  \n- **Common Pok\u00e9mon:**  \n  - Alolan and Galarian forms (e.g., Alolan Meowth, Galarian Farfetch\u2019d), as well as baby Pok\u00e9mon like Cleffa, Igglybuff, Togepi, and more.  \n- **Event-exclusive Pok\u00e9mon may also appear during special events.**\n\n### 4. **10 km Eggs**  \n- **Common Pok\u00e9mon:**  \n  - Jangmo-o, Goomy, Riolu, Axew, Deino, Gible, Darumaka, and more.  \n- **Event-exclusive Pok\u00e9mon may also appear during special events.**\n\n### 5. **12 km Eggs (Strange Eggs)**  \n- **Common Pok\u00e9mon:**  \n  - Vullaby, Pawniard, Larvitar, Scraggy, Deino, Skorupi, and more. These Eggs are obtained by defeating Team GO Rocket leaders.  \n\n### 6. **Event Eggs**  \nDuring special events, Niantic sometimes introduces unique Eggs with specific Pok\u00e9mon that are only available for a limited time.  \n\n### Notes:  \n- Egg pools are updated periodically, so the available Pok\u00e9mon can change.  \n- Some Pok\u00e9mon may have a higher rarity in Eggs, making them harder to hatch.  \n- Check the in-game Egg section for the most up-to-date list of hatchable Pok\u00e9mon.  \n\nLet me know if you\u2019d like more details!",
